Description: This Eddie Vedder signed vintage Danelectro guitar is being auctioned to help pay final production costs for the Return to Mt. Kennedy film and promote its positive message. A portion of the proceeds will also go to Ferry County Rail Trail Partners, a non-profit organization dear to Eddie Vedder and Bobby Whittaker. The lyrics from the song Rise are also handwritten by Eddie on the back. Early 1960s Silvertone/Danelectro guitar. Marketed in Sears Catalog. Danelectro U1 model 1317 with single "lipstick" pickup copper with original case. Signed by Eddie Vedder along with lyrics from Rise on the back. Bonus autograph on the case by Eddie and also by Matt Lukin, the original bassist for Mudhoney who also appears in the film. Also an assortment of EV guitar picks from Eddie's personal collection. First group photo is from the 12/9 showing at the Seattle Cinerama. Left to right: Leif, Bobby and Jim Whittaker and film director Eric Becker. Second group photo is from the presentation for 12/9 - Jim Whittaker Day. Left to right: Eric Becker, Executive of King County - Dow Constantine, Eddie, Bobby, Jim and Leif Whittaker. About the Film: In 1965 Jim Whittaker led Robert Kennedy on the first ascent of a remote mountain in the Yukon named after JFK. Fifty years later, their sons revisit the site of the iconic climb to learn more about the endeavor that shaped their families. Return to Mount Kennedy spans generations, reminding how every trail connects through the enduring friendships built in the mountains. Featuring interviews and several new instrumentals by Eddie Vedder and never before seen footage of the climb, the film sits at the intersection of politics, human rights, environmentalism, and adventure. Find out more at mtkennedy dot com and follow us on Facebook. Thanks to everyone for bidding! Buyer pays all shipping costs including duty and other international fees where they apply. Please be advised: bidders from outside of the U.S.A. must contact us prior to bidding to clarify shipping arrangements and costs. We reserve the right to cancel bids of buyers with one or zero feedback.On Dec-12-18 at 12:56:14 PST, seller added the following information: Some viewers have already noticed that the guitar picks are indeed very special to Eddie. An example are two that have T.P. on one side and an Oscar on the other.
